The donuts were fresh and delicious! He also told me about the rewards program (which I will be joining soon). Because of the interaction I had with him on this weekend, I decided to stop by again today. When I went back today, I had the pleasure of encountering employees Sophie and Laura- They were so sweet! Two words...... ghe toe!  Come on folks we have got to do better. The 125th St location so far is a let down to this well known franchise. When I arrived I was “greeted” by a less than hospitable security guard. Instead of inviting me in she informed me of all the donut flavors not available. Now i’m confused because unlike some other locations that have the donuts delivered, this location is a baking facility. No excuses, all the varieties should be available. The security guard did not disappoint..... she was right. It seemed as though the only flavor they had was the original glazed. You could clearly see within the display case there were glazed donuts everywhere. This is bad management. No way a good manager would allow their newly famous franchise to run out of that many flavors. Anyway, the place looked cleaned. I was served right away, didn’t notice if anyone was wearing a mask. Mainly because I was focused on getting in n out. If your in the area and have a craving stop in. If you want anything other than the original glazed get on the train and go downtown to the other locations. If this opening is any indication of how this location is managed  I feel sorry for the people who work there.
